Image supplied By Andile Mngxitama The Azanian National Liberation Army (AZANLA) was the military wing of the Black Consciousness Movement (BCM) represented by the Azanian People’s Organisation (AZAPO). It‘s the youngest of the liberation armies of our people. We salute the young men and women of our nation who were prepared to lay down their lives so that we may be free. We respect all the armies of the liberation movement – AZANLA of AZAPO, the Azanian People’s Liberation Army (APLA) of the Pan Africanist Congress of Azania (PAC), and Umkhonto we Sizwe (MK) of the African National Congress (ANC). Long live the spirit of the AZANLA fighters who died fighting! We shall never forget the sacrifices they have made to the struggle. The struggle continues… Land or Death!!! Andile Mngxitama is the President of Black First Land First (BLF), a radical black consciousness organization.